?CSV File Chunker - Splits large CSV files into smaller chunks

Usage: java Main [options]


Options:
M  -i, --input <dir>       Input directory containing CSV files (default: .)
D  -o, --output <dir>      Output directory for chunks (default: .)
A  -s, --size <MB>         Maximum chunk size in MB (default: 9)
F  -h, --header <bool>     Write header to each chunk (default: true)
S  -p, --pattern <pat>     File name pattern (default: {name}-chunk-{counter}.csv)
;                          Placeholders: {name}, {counter}
2  -?, --help              Show this help message

Examples:
(  java Main -i ./data -o ./chunks -s 5
2  java Main --pattern "data-{counter}.csv" -s 10
Starting file chunking...

Input: .
Output: .
Max file size: 9 MB
Write header: true
*File pattern: {name}-chunk-{counter}.csv

Done!
